The paper discusses the use of neuromorphic multi-chip systems (NMSs) for training probabilistic topic models. NMSs are a type of hardware technology that is particularly effective for spiking neural networks (SNNs), which are used in the proposed algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses unsupervised learning methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves stochastic optimization, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
